description: BusyBox is a versatile embedded Linux toolset, version 1.13.0, compiled on 2013-08-29. This version may contain known security vulnerabilities, and it is recommended to check relevant CVEs.
uClibc is a commonly used C standard library in embedded systems, version 1.7.0. This version is relatively old and may pose security risks.
The GCC compiler version 4.2.3 was used to compile this firmware. This is a relatively old version that may contain known vulnerabilities.
